#31300
the Pine Forest~
   The main thoroughfare to the North is to the west.  Looking north or south
will train your eyes just inside the tree line on the shoulder of the road.  
The ground is moist, thick with pine straw and moss.  The soil is rich, so the
trees grow very tall here.  The forest is teaming with vegetation, wild game,
and insects.  To the east the forest gets a bit darker as the towering trees
block a great portion of natural light.  The air is clean smells fresh of the
pine sap and campfire.  
~
